import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.figure(figsize=(10, 6))
    sns.histplot(data=data, x='normal', kde=True, color='blue', alpha=0.5)
    median_normal = data['normal'].median()
    plt.axvline(median_normal, color='red', linestyle='--', label=f'Median: {median_normal:.2f}')
    plt.xlabel('Normal Values')
    plt.ylabel('Frequency')
    plt.title("What is the distribution of 'normal' values in the dataset?", wrap=True)
    plt.legend()
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['day'] = pd.to_datetime(data['day'], errors='coerce')
    data = data[pd.notna(data['day'])]

    plt.figure(figsize=(12, 6))
    sns.lineplot(x='day', y='actual', data=data, label='Actual')
    sns.lineplot(x='day', y='forecast', data=data, label='Forecast')
    plt.title("How do the 'actual' values compare to the 'forecast' values?", wrap=True)
    plt.xlabel('Day')
    plt.ylabel('Values')
    plt.legend()
    plt.xticks(rotation=45)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['day'] = pd.to_datetime(data['day'], errors='coerce')
    data = data[pd.notna(data['day'])]
    data['day'] = data['day'].dt.strftime('%Y-%m-%d')

    day_count = data['day'].value_counts().reset_index()
    day_count.columns = ['day', 'count']

    plt.figure(figsize=(10, 6))
    sns.barplot(x='day', y='count', data=day_count, palette='viridis')
    plt.xticks(rotation=45)
    plt.xlabel('Day')
    plt.ylabel('Record Count')
    plt.title("What is the frequency of records by 'day'?", wrap=True)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

    plt.title("What is the distribution of 'id' values in the dataset?", wrap=True)
    plt.legend()
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):

    sns.scatterplot(data=data, x='normal', y='actual')

    plt.xlabel("Normal Values")
    plt.ylabel("Actual Values")

    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
